-- China Sells 10-Year Government Bonds at 3.41-Percent Yield, Traders Say
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-23T02:35:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/china-sells-10-year-government-bonds-at-3-41-percent-yield-traders-say.html

          
          
             China’s finance ministry sold 28
billion yuan ($4.1 billion) of 10-year bonds at an average yield
of 3.41 percent, according to traders at Bank of China Ltd. and
BOC International (China) Ltd. in Beijing.  
 The highest winning-bid yield was 3.45 percent, said the
traders at the primary dealers required to bid at the government
auctions.  
 The average yield at today’s auction was 2 basis points
higher than the 3.39 percent median estimate in a Bloomberg News
survey of 10 finance companies. A basis point is 0.01 percentage
point.  
 -- Belinda Cao . Editor:  Nerys Avery   
